qas.question: What year was the Sakya viceregal regime eradicated?
Who placed the Sakya viceregal regime position of authority?
Who eradicated the Sakya viceregal regime?

answers.text: the Phagmodru myriarch Tai Situ Changchub Gyaltsen

qas.question: Which dynasty became ruler of Tibet?

context: In <a0_0>1358<a0_0/>, the Sakya viceregal regime installed by <a1_0>the Mongols in Tibet<a1_0/> was overthrown in a rebellion by <a2_0>the Phagmodru myriarch Tai Situ Changchub Gyaltsen<a2_0/> (1302–1364). The Mongol Yuan court was forced to accept him as the new viceroy, and Changchub Gyaltsen and his successors, <a3_0>the Phagmodrupa Dynasty<a3_0/>, gained de facto rule over Tibet.
